  "title": "SOFTWARE AND APPLICATIONS MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p><ol><li>Provide IT systems administration and technical support for engineering and R&D teams, including workstation setup, software deployment, system troubleshooting, and network access management.</li><li>Manage internal business and engineering software platforms, supporting configuration, user training, permission control, and process improvements.</li><li>Coordinate troubleshooting and support for system issues affecting design tools, computing infrastructure, or internal applications.</li><li>Monitor system performance and cybersecurity safeguards, implementing best practices, including endpoint protection and access controls.</li><li>Support cross-functional technology projects to enhance system stability, efficiency,\nand collaboration across engineering teams.</li></ol><p></p><p>Requirements:</p><ol><li>Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering, Information Technology, Computer Science, or related disciplines.</li><li>Minimum 5 years of relevant experience in IT\nsystems engineering or technical support roles, preferably within semiconductor\nor advanced technology environments.</li><li>Familiarity with Windows operating systems,\nuser account management, and access control procedures.</li><li>Strong communication and coordination skills to work effectively\nwith engineers, project teams, vendors, and internal stakeholders.</li></ol><p><br /></p>",
